<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WOMEN’S PRIZE FOR FICTION</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Awarded to a female author of any nationality for the best original full-length novel written in English and published in the UK.<br />
Prize Money: £30,000</em></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-medium wp-image-131124 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/05/0d15123d87d27535132a3444754df6e1-198x300.gif" sizes="auto, (max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/05/0d15123d87d27535132a3444754df6e1-198x300.gif 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/05/0d15123d87d27535132a3444754df6e1-33x50.gif 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/05/0d15123d87d27535132a3444754df6e1.gif 427w" alt="Van Der Wouden, Yael_The Safekeep Cover" width="198" height="300" data-attachment-id="131124" data-permalink="https://bookmarks.reviews/bookmark/the-safekeep/the-safekeep-cover/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/05/0d15123d87d27535132a3444754df6e1.gif" data-orig-size="427,648" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Van Der Wouden, Yael_The Safekeep Cover" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/05/0d15123d87d27535132a3444754df6e1-198x300.gif" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/05/0d15123d87d27535132a3444754df6e1.gif" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="https://bookmarks.reviews/reviews/the-safekeep/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Safekeeping</em></a> by Yael Van Der Wouden</strong><br />
<strong>(Avid Reader Press)</strong></p>
<p>“What a quietly remarkable book … Nothing in this book is gratuitous. Van der Wouden’s writing is fine and taut. She lasers in on details, and presents unsentimental and intrinsically powerful metaphors … The story is resolved in such a bold and tender way that it becomes not merely clever, but indelible.”</p>
<p style="text-align: right;">–Lori Soderlind (<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/05/25/books/review/safekeep-yael-van-der-wouden.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The New York Times Book Review</em></a>)</p>
<p><strong>Finalists:</strong></p>
<p>Aria Aber, <a href="https://bookmarks.reviews/reviews/good-girl/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Good Girl </em></a>(Hogarth)<br />
Miranda July, <a href="https://bookmarks.reviews/reviews/all-fours/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>All Fours</em></a> (Riverhead)<br />
